Active and Passive Metrics and Methods
(with Hybrid Types In-Between)
2016", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC7799.html", target="_top", tooltip="This memo provides clear definitions for Active and Passive performance assessment.  The construction of Metrics and Methods can be described as either Active or Passive.  Some methods may use a subset of both Active and Passive attributes, and we refer to these as Hybrid Methods.  This memo also describes multiple dimensions to help evaluate new methods as they emerge."];
  cites -> RFC7799;
  RFC2119 [label="RFC2119
Key words for use in RFCs to Indicate
Requirement Levels
1997", shape=ellipse, URL="RFC2119.html", target="_top", tooltip="In many standards track documents several words are used to signify the requirements in the specification.  These words are often capitalized.  This document defines these words as they should be interpreted in IETF documents.  This document specifies an Internet Best Current Practices for the Internet Community, and requests discussion and suggestions for improvements."];
